WEBVTT

00:06.966 --> 00:08.259
Previously on
The Summer I Turned Pretty...

00:08.342 --> 00:09.635
I just have, there's just
so much shit going on.

00:09.719 --> 00:11.345
If we started something,

00:11.429 --> 00:12.847
I feel like I could
fuck it up.

00:12.930 --> 00:14.849
- I need to talk to my sister.
- She's with Jeremiah.

00:14.932 --> 00:16.600
[Taylor] Conrad was MIA,
but they figured out

00:16.684 --> 00:17.643
that he's in Cousins,
so they're on their way

00:17.727 --> 00:18.686
to go get him right now.

00:18.769 --> 00:20.062
I'm pissed about last summer.

00:20.146 --> 00:21.397
Belly, you were my best friend.

00:21.480 --> 00:23.065
We hooked up.

00:23.149 --> 00:24.942
And then you hooked up
with my brother, and then

00:25.025 --> 00:26.360
everyone expected me
to act like I was fine.

00:26.444 --> 00:27.445
And I wasn't!

00:27.528 --> 00:29.989
I hate that I let you down.

00:30.072 --> 00:32.950
[Conrad] Jere, the house
has been put up for sale.

00:33.033 --> 00:34.201
What do you mean,
the house is for sale?

00:34.285 --> 00:35.786
What is she doing here?

00:39.165 --> 00:41.167
♪ ♪

00:48.632 --> 00:49.800
[Jeremiah] So this is
why you haven't

00:49.884 --> 00:51.469
answered any of my phone calls

00:51.552 --> 00:53.095
- and texts?
- Jere. Jere.

00:53.179 --> 00:54.346
Did you not hear
what I just said?

00:54.430 --> 00:56.766
We're going to lose this house.
Mom's house.

00:56.849 --> 00:58.809
- Why would your dad
sell this house?
- He's not.

00:58.893 --> 01:01.896
- Our Aunt Julia is.
- Susannah's sister?

01:01.979 --> 01:04.063
Half sister. Apparently,

01:04.147 --> 01:06.567
the house belonged to the both
of them. And then when Mom...

01:06.650 --> 01:10.070
Now Aunt Julia
owns the whole thing, so...

01:10.154 --> 01:11.697
Okay, we'll just call Dad
and figure something out.

01:11.781 --> 01:12.948
- That's it.
- You think I haven't
already done that?

01:13.032 --> 01:14.533
He says legally
the house is hers.

01:14.617 --> 01:15.868
Okay, then he'll buy it.

01:15.951 --> 01:17.328
He doesn't have
the money to buy it.

01:17.411 --> 01:19.038
Between Brown and
the medical bills and the...

01:19.121 --> 01:20.998
Yeah, I know how much
the medical bills cost

01:21.081 --> 01:22.333
because I was there.

01:23.918 --> 01:26.295
How long did you know
about this and not tell me?

01:26.378 --> 01:28.214
Jere, this was all
happening so fast.

01:28.297 --> 01:30.382
I was going to tell you
after I'd taken care of it.

01:30.466 --> 01:32.634
[chuckles] And this is
you taking care of it?

01:32.718 --> 01:34.011
Going AWOL, ditching school,

01:34.094 --> 01:35.346
- not talking to us.
- Fuck school!

01:35.429 --> 01:37.014
- I don't care!
- Connie, you have to go back

01:37.097 --> 01:38.598
- or you'll fail your class.
- How are you going to become

01:38.682 --> 01:41.602
a doctor if you fail
out of college, Conrad?

01:41.685 --> 01:43.896
You have no idea
what you're talking about.

01:45.606 --> 01:46.732
Seriously?

01:46.816 --> 01:50.860
We went to Brown
to check on your ass.

01:50.945 --> 01:53.322
You know what? I didn't think
you'd pull this shit again.

01:53.405 --> 01:55.533
But you don't give a shit
about anyone but yourself.

02:00.788 --> 02:03.374
[door opens in distance]

02:03.415 --> 02:05.167
[door closes]

02:07.920 --> 02:10.047
[Belly] He won't
even look at me.

02:12.466 --> 02:14.385
Sorry if me being here is weird.

02:16.011 --> 02:17.972
So, the-the house...

02:18.055 --> 02:21.475
It's for sale.
And Jere doesn't even care.

02:21.559 --> 02:25.603
Of course he cares.
But he cares about you more.

02:25.688 --> 02:29.483
After everything
that happened...

02:29.567 --> 02:31.068
you go missing?

02:31.151 --> 02:35.281
I mean, he thought something
really bad happened to you.

02:35.364 --> 02:36.824
We both did.

02:38.826 --> 02:40.870
I got a call two days ago.

02:41.912 --> 02:43.454
From Liam.

02:43.539 --> 02:46.959
He was asking me about a "for
sale" sign in our front yard.

02:47.042 --> 02:48.210
I thought
it was a misunderstanding,

02:48.293 --> 02:50.462
so I drove straight here.
I pulled the stupid sign

02:50.546 --> 02:54.174
out of the ground,
and I threw it in the garbage.

02:54.258 --> 02:56.635
Seeing that sign was like
losing her all over again,

02:56.719 --> 02:59.054
and I didn't want that for Jere.

03:00.055 --> 03:02.600
I'm going to use my trust
as down payment for the house.

03:02.683 --> 03:04.685
Talking to my mom's
financial guys in the morning.

03:04.768 --> 03:06.312
Oh.

03:06.395 --> 03:08.063
I didn't mean to worry anybody.

03:08.147 --> 03:10.649
I'm handling things.
You guys can go.

03:11.942 --> 03:14.820
You're not the only one
who cares about this house.

03:16.113 --> 03:18.032
If Jere wants to stay here
and help figure things out,

03:18.115 --> 03:20.200
that is his decision.

03:20.284 --> 03:21.994
And you don't get
to make it for him.

03:27.374 --> 03:29.376
♪ ♪

03:32.630 --> 03:35.841
[Belly] There is nothing
more beautiful than this.

03:35.925 --> 03:38.928
This particular sunset.

03:39.011 --> 03:40.679
It can match
the beauty of anything

03:40.763 --> 03:43.849
in this world ten times over.

03:43.933 --> 03:46.894
No matter what's happened,
you can feel the tension

03:46.977 --> 03:50.731
of the day drifting away
and out to sea.

03:50.814 --> 03:55.152
I want to memorize it all,
because...

03:55.235 --> 03:57.988
you never know the last time
you'll see a place,

03:58.072 --> 04:00.074
a person.

04:06.163 --> 04:07.957
[sighs]

04:11.794 --> 04:13.796
You'd think
someone would have invented

04:13.879 --> 04:15.464
an easier system by now.

04:15.547 --> 04:18.425
If I wasn't so fucking tired,
I'd probably leave tonight.

04:19.426 --> 04:21.095
My mom would always
fix everything up

04:21.178 --> 04:22.888
before we got here.

04:22.972 --> 04:26.517
Yeah. The house feels different
without her in it.

04:26.600 --> 04:28.894
I'm still so pissed at Conrad.
I mean, what is he even

04:28.978 --> 04:31.271
talking about
with this whole house thing?

04:31.355 --> 04:32.773
I think it's for real.

04:35.651 --> 04:36.902
Shit.

04:39.029 --> 04:40.614
[Jeremiah sighs]

04:42.408 --> 04:44.076
[laughs softly]

04:45.577 --> 04:48.414
You're just going to sleep
on it like that, aren't you?

04:48.497 --> 04:50.207
- Yep.
- Yeah.

04:55.004 --> 04:56.171
Hey, Belly.

04:58.048 --> 04:59.258
Yeah?

04:59.341 --> 05:01.301
Um, thank you
for coming with me.

05:01.385 --> 05:04.847
I don't know what went down
between you and Conrad,

05:04.930 --> 05:07.307
but I know it couldn't
be easy to be here.

05:09.226 --> 05:11.645
I'm glad I don't have
to do this alone.

05:11.729 --> 05:14.273
Yeah, I'm glad I came, too.

05:16.608 --> 05:19.278
- Good night.
- Good night.

05:26.994 --> 05:29.246
[Belly] The truth is, the
hardest part about being here

05:29.329 --> 05:30.706
isn't Conrad.

05:30.789 --> 05:32.750
Back home,
I can almost believe

05:32.832 --> 05:34.752
Susannah isn't really gone.

05:34.835 --> 05:36.795
But here at the beach house,

05:36.879 --> 05:38.756
she's everywhere

05:38.839 --> 05:40.841
and nowhere.

05:42.843 --> 05:44.845
♪ ♪

06:06.408 --> 06:09.495
♪ ♪

06:17.002 --> 06:19.046
Do you still pretend
you're in the Olympics?

06:19.129 --> 06:21.715
Uh, no. Not-not anymore.

06:22.758 --> 06:24.718
When you swim,

06:24.802 --> 06:28.013
I don't think you'd notice
if the house was on fire.

06:29.348 --> 06:30.891
You're so into
what you're doing.

06:30.974 --> 06:32.976
It's like you're someplace else.

06:35.145 --> 06:36.980
That's what I like about it.

07:02.714 --> 07:04.299
[Conrad] I know. But you're
sure there's no way to access

07:04.383 --> 07:05.843
my trust without him?

07:06.969 --> 07:10.389
No, I haven't...
talked to him about it just yet.

07:10.472 --> 07:12.724
But, um, it won't be a problem.

07:12.808 --> 07:15.561
He's calling soon
and I'll get him to sign off.

07:17.187 --> 07:20.107
Okay. Yeah. Thank you.

07:23.360 --> 07:24.570
Morning.

07:26.321 --> 07:28.240
You want to talk about a plan B?

07:28.323 --> 07:30.117
There's no time
for a plan B, Jere.

07:30.200 --> 07:31.618
There's no time?
Come on, dude.

07:31.702 --> 07:32.953
Is your ego really that big
or is...?

07:33.036 --> 07:34.538
Aunt Julia is already here.

07:34.621 --> 07:36.999
- What?
- Yeah, she got in yesterday.

07:37.082 --> 07:39.585
- She's at Ocean Harbor.
- You saw her?

07:39.668 --> 07:41.795
I mean, we talked on the phone
for about five seconds.

07:41.879 --> 07:44.173
She couldn't be bothered
to come to Mom's funeral,

07:44.256 --> 07:45.465
but she'll hop on
the first flight

07:45.549 --> 07:46.550
to come sell this place.

07:46.633 --> 07:47.968
I don't get it. Why?

07:48.051 --> 07:49.636
- What's the big rush?
- It doesn't matter why.

07:49.720 --> 07:53.432
This isn't a game, okay?
This is serious shit.

07:53.515 --> 07:56.518
So just go back to bed
and let me deal with it.

07:59.688 --> 08:01.023
[door opens]

08:01.106 --> 08:02.941
- That went well.
- [door closes]

08:03.984 --> 08:06.862
You know, he keeps saying
he's going to figure things out.

08:06.945 --> 08:09.364
He hasn't figured out shit.

08:09.448 --> 08:11.325
Can-can you talk some sense
into him?

08:11.408 --> 08:14.244
You are the only person
that can get through to Conrad.

08:14.328 --> 08:16.038
[Belly] Did you
get your tux yet?

08:19.291 --> 08:21.376
Oh, n...

08:21.460 --> 08:23.045
I still have time, right?

08:23.128 --> 08:24.922
Prom's not until, like, the 2nd.

08:25.005 --> 08:26.548
Uh, the 1st.

08:27.549 --> 08:28.842
The fir...

08:28.926 --> 08:30.969
- Hey, Connie.
- Hey, Laurel.

08:31.053 --> 08:33.347
Belly, you might study better
in an actual chair.

08:33.429 --> 08:35.390
No, I-I think better
from up here.

08:37.851 --> 08:41.395
Oh, um, we have to pitch in
our share if we want to get

08:41.480 --> 08:44.066
- that hotel suite
with Taylor and her date.
- Mm-hmm.

08:44.149 --> 08:47.319
Wow. Talking about getting a
hotel room right in front of me.

08:47.402 --> 08:50.322
- I must be a cool mom now.
- No. Ew! Mom.

08:50.405 --> 08:51.865
It's just so
we can hang out after.

08:51.949 --> 08:53.575
- Okay.
- Yeah. No, you know that.

08:53.659 --> 08:56.411
[laughs nervously]

09:00.415 --> 09:01.959
Do you want me
to order your tux?

09:02.042 --> 09:04.044
No. No, I got it.

09:06.588 --> 09:07.965
[quietly] Okay.

09:13.095 --> 09:17.724
- Is everything okay?
- Yeah, I just forgot the date.

09:19.768 --> 09:21.228
Okay.

09:27.734 --> 09:31.697
My mom's doctors are considering
putting her on new meds.

09:31.780 --> 09:35.158
Which must mean that the
current ones stopped working.

09:35.242 --> 09:36.868
[sighs]

09:36.952 --> 09:39.121
- Oh, okay.
- Sorry.

09:39.204 --> 09:42.040
- I'm not trying to worry you.
- No, no, no, no, stop it.

09:42.124 --> 09:44.501
You can talk to me
about anything.

09:44.584 --> 09:46.712
Especially Susannah.

09:49.339 --> 09:51.091
My mom always gets really down

09:51.174 --> 09:52.718
when Susannah's
going through it.

09:52.801 --> 09:54.678
And she's clearly
in a good enough mood today

09:54.761 --> 09:56.722
to think that she's funny.

09:56.805 --> 09:59.224
I'm sure the new meds
just means she's doing better

09:59.308 --> 10:01.977
and she needs
a smaller dose or something.

10:02.019 --> 10:04.146
[sighs]

10:04.229 --> 10:05.772
Yeah.

10:07.107 --> 10:09.359
Yeah, I'm sure you're right.

10:11.361 --> 10:12.821
[Belly] I didn't know it then,

10:12.904 --> 10:14.823
but I was already losing him.

10:18.160 --> 10:21.204
Uh, Conrad may have
listened to me at one point,

10:21.288 --> 10:24.374
but I don't think
he cares what I think anymore.

10:24.416 --> 10:25.917
Mm.

10:26.001 --> 10:29.588
I'm hungry. Are you...
you hungry?

10:34.885 --> 10:37.971
Man, Susannah used
to have this place filled

10:38.055 --> 10:39.348
to the brim before we got here.

10:39.431 --> 10:40.891
I can get something.

10:40.974 --> 10:43.769
Can make some frittatas.

10:43.852 --> 10:47.064
The grocery store
is right next to Ocean Harbor.

10:49.775 --> 10:52.402
We're going to go
find Aunt Julia.

10:52.486 --> 10:54.154
We're going to go find
Aunt Julia.

10:54.237 --> 10:55.906
All right.

10:57.657 --> 11:00.035
♪ ♪

11:05.040 --> 11:06.583
[Laurel] I'm headed
to the train station.

11:06.666 --> 11:08.835
Uh, kick ass.

11:08.919 --> 11:10.670
Or, I mean, you know,
whatever you're supposed to do

11:10.754 --> 11:13.507
- at these things.
- [chuckles] Your guess is
as good as mine.

11:16.093 --> 11:17.844
Hey, have you heard
from Belly today?

11:17.928 --> 11:19.513
I'm only getting one-word texts.

11:19.596 --> 11:21.973
Uh, yeah. Yes, me, too.

11:22.057 --> 11:23.392
You think I should call her?

11:23.475 --> 11:25.727
No, no, no, she's fine, Mom.

11:25.811 --> 11:27.979
I actually got her up to
three-word answers this morning,

11:28.063 --> 11:29.940
so she's coming around.

11:30.023 --> 11:34.236
Like, she'll probably be back
from Taylor's soon. Yeah?

11:34.319 --> 11:36.071
Okay.

11:36.154 --> 11:37.906
Well, I'll only be gone
a few days,

11:37.989 --> 11:40.075
but remember,
trash goes out Wednesday

11:40.158 --> 11:41.410
and the grass needs cutting.

11:41.493 --> 11:43.578
And honestly, Steven,
it would be nice if

11:43.662 --> 11:45.205
you could put your clothes away.

11:45.288 --> 11:46.957
I love you, Mom.

11:47.040 --> 11:49.126
Yeah, I love you, too.

11:50.419 --> 11:52.504
- Bye.
- Mwah. Safe travels. Okay?

11:52.587 --> 11:53.797
Thank you.

11:53.880 --> 11:55.966
- Don't forget.
- I won't.

11:56.049 --> 11:57.259
[door closes]

11:57.342 --> 11:59.886
[sighs heavily]

11:59.970 --> 12:02.389
- [panting]
- [phone ringing]

12:09.771 --> 12:11.857
[groans]
What do you want, Steven?

12:11.940 --> 12:13.608
I'm going to Cousins.

12:13.692 --> 12:15.527
Wait. I-I thought you said
that you were going to let Belly

12:15.610 --> 12:16.945
handle this on her own.

12:17.028 --> 12:19.448
Yes, uh, I was, but, you know,

12:19.531 --> 12:21.658
Conrad called
and asked me to come.

12:21.741 --> 12:23.660
Look, this is their first summer
without their mom, okay?

12:23.743 --> 12:24.995
They need me.

12:25.078 --> 12:26.913
- [sighs]
- And, you know,

12:26.997 --> 12:29.708
with Belly still
being sad over Conrad,

12:29.791 --> 12:31.126
I mean, the two of them
there together,

12:31.209 --> 12:32.377
that's, you know... [exhales]

12:32.461 --> 12:36.465
It's actually
kind of sweet of you.

12:36.548 --> 12:37.966
Well, what are you going
to tell Laurel?

12:38.049 --> 12:40.051
Okay? Because I can't
cover for both of you.

12:40.135 --> 12:41.470
I'm stressed out about this.

12:41.553 --> 12:43.054
Yeah, I wasn't asking you to.

12:43.138 --> 12:44.431
Okay? She's going out of town
for a couple days

12:44.514 --> 12:45.599
for some book thing.

12:45.682 --> 12:47.267
Anyways, um, I just,

12:47.350 --> 12:48.685
I just wanted to let you know.

12:48.768 --> 12:50.729
Cool.

12:50.770 --> 12:52.814
[sighs]

12:52.898 --> 12:54.399
Well, I-I'm coming with you,

12:54.483 --> 12:55.901
actually.

12:55.984 --> 12:58.570
[chuckles] Uh, why?

12:58.653 --> 13:00.363
I thought you hated Cousins.

13:00.447 --> 13:02.532
No, I don't hate Cousins.

13:02.616 --> 13:05.994
I hate annoying rich people
who leave me naked in the woods.

13:06.077 --> 13:07.829
But, I mean, there's no way

13:07.913 --> 13:09.122
that I'm just going to stay here

13:09.206 --> 13:10.582
while you guys are all
together in Cousins.

13:10.665 --> 13:13.502
[exhales] I mean, I guess
splitting the driving time

13:13.585 --> 13:15.545
with someone wouldn't be
the worst thing in the world.

13:15.629 --> 13:17.339
Okay, okay, but, but...

13:17.422 --> 13:18.715
I am leaving, like, right now.

13:18.798 --> 13:19.883
Okay? Seriously.

13:19.966 --> 13:21.218
Yeah, no, I-I swear
I'll be packed

13:21.301 --> 13:22.969
and ready
by the time you get here.

13:23.053 --> 13:25.555
Um, also, one more thing.
I'm-I'm going to send you a list

13:25.639 --> 13:27.140
of things to pack
for Belly, okay?

13:27.224 --> 13:28.934
Because I'm sure
that she's been in,

13:29.017 --> 13:30.519
like, the same big T-shirt

13:30.602 --> 13:32.354
this entire time.

13:32.437 --> 13:33.605
Yeah. Okay. Bye.

13:33.688 --> 13:35.690
- Bye.
- Yeah.

13:41.196 --> 13:43.573
So what's our game plan
with Julia, huh?

13:43.657 --> 13:46.076
- Hmm.
- Sneak attack? Bribery?

13:46.159 --> 13:47.661
Murder?

13:47.744 --> 13:49.496
Wow. Um,

13:49.579 --> 13:52.040
I was thinking that we just
play to my strengths.

13:53.083 --> 13:54.793
So charm offensive.

13:54.876 --> 13:56.336
Hence the flowers.

13:56.419 --> 13:57.671
- Exactly.
- Okay.

13:57.754 --> 13:59.172
You know, I wish I had
more to go on,

13:59.256 --> 14:01.883
but she and my mom
weren't exactly close.

14:01.967 --> 14:03.802
I mean, the last time
I saw her and Skye,

14:03.885 --> 14:06.388
I was probably, like,
seven, eight years old.

14:06.471 --> 14:09.182
- Wow, that's a long time.
- Yeah.

14:09.266 --> 14:12.310
You know, I remember
Susannah telling me that it was

14:12.394 --> 14:14.896
her big sister who convinced her
that she could be an artist.

14:16.356 --> 14:17.357
Really?

14:18.942 --> 14:20.610
You know, honestly,
I don't really remember much

14:20.694 --> 14:23.280
about her,
so I'll-I'll just wing it.

14:23.363 --> 14:25.031
And knowing Conrad,
he probably took

14:25.115 --> 14:26.866
the righteous anger route
when he talked with her.

14:26.950 --> 14:30.537
And I'm sure that
went over like gangbusters.

14:30.620 --> 14:32.664
Yeah, Conrad's never
been good at putting on

14:32.747 --> 14:35.417
a happy face
when he's not feeling it.

14:35.500 --> 14:38.003
[Laurel] Okay, let's get
the boys in here, too.

14:38.086 --> 14:39.045
[Conrad] About time.

14:39.129 --> 14:40.714
Oh, don't look so excited.

14:40.797 --> 14:42.799
- I know.
- [indistinct chatter]

14:44.092 --> 14:46.303
Prom poses?

14:46.386 --> 14:48.847
Laurel, you-you got,
you got a full-body shot, right?

14:48.930 --> 14:50.974
And-and I want,
I want the back

14:51.057 --> 14:52.267
of Belly's hair,
not just the front.

14:52.350 --> 14:53.977
- Beck.
- I'm sorry, Laurel,

14:54.060 --> 14:55.353
but you suck
at taking pictures.

14:55.437 --> 14:56.479
Hey!

14:56.563 --> 14:57.981
- [laughter]
- You do.

14:58.064 --> 14:59.524
- [Laurel] Love it.
- [camera clicks]

14:59.608 --> 15:01.401
- [Susannah] Let me see
their corsages.
- Yeah.

15:01.484 --> 15:04.613
Do you, do you...?

15:05.780 --> 15:08.325
- Shit.
- What's wrong?

15:08.408 --> 15:09.826
I don't have your corsage.

15:09.909 --> 15:14.080
I must have left it
in my dorm fridge.

15:16.541 --> 15:17.876
[quietly] It's okay.

15:20.211 --> 15:21.379
Okay, we got to go.

15:21.463 --> 15:22.672
- Yes.
- Right.

15:22.756 --> 15:24.341
[Laurel] Beck, it's time
for them to head out.

15:24.424 --> 15:25.842
I'm gonna get
a couple last pics, okay?

15:25.925 --> 15:28.511
And I'm heading up to you
tomorrow, first thing.

15:31.556 --> 15:33.975
- You okay?
- I'm so sorry I forgot.

15:34.059 --> 15:35.268
I should've remembered it.

15:35.352 --> 15:36.686
Don't worry about the corsage.

15:36.770 --> 15:37.979
Seriously, it's...

15:39.773 --> 15:41.691
You'll just
have to get me two corsages

15:41.775 --> 15:43.109
next year to make up for it.

15:43.193 --> 15:45.195
Wear one on each wrist.

15:45.278 --> 15:47.572
Whatever you want.

15:51.660 --> 15:54.079
- [indistinct chatter]
- ♪ ♪

16:01.544 --> 16:04.172
- Shall we? Mm-hmm.
- Thank you.

16:04.255 --> 16:06.466
- Gentleman.
- [Steven chuckles]

16:08.593 --> 16:11.554
You gonna ask my sister
to dance or what, Fisher?

16:15.892 --> 16:17.352
Do you want to dance?

16:17.435 --> 16:19.729
Uh, we don't have to,
if you don't want to.

16:32.409 --> 16:35.412
[♪ The Smashing Pumpkins:
"Mayonaise"]

16:58.268 --> 17:01.938
♪ Fool enough to almost be it ♪

17:02.021 --> 17:04.065
♪ Cool enough
to not quite see it...

17:04.148 --> 17:05.942
I'm glad you're here.

17:06.025 --> 17:08.611
Me, too.

17:11.906 --> 17:15.410
♪ Pick your pocket,
full of sorrow ♪

17:15.492 --> 17:18.246
♪ Run away with me tomorrow ♪

17:18.329 --> 17:20.123
♪ June...

17:20.205 --> 17:22.250
Do you want to go somewhere?

17:22.333 --> 17:26.421
Well, um, well, the after-prom
doesn't start till midnight.

17:26.503 --> 17:28.840
Right, no, I mean,
just you and me.

17:28.923 --> 17:31.050
Do you want to go
somewhere we can talk?

17:31.134 --> 17:32.927
♪ Somehow...

17:33.011 --> 17:35.096
No, let's not go anywhere.

17:35.180 --> 17:37.474
Let's just, let's,
let's stay here for a while.

17:38.725 --> 17:40.685
All right.

17:44.105 --> 17:46.024
I just might
go back to school tonight.

17:46.107 --> 17:48.318
I have an exam on Monday
and everything.

17:49.861 --> 17:51.321
- Oh.
- Is it all right

17:51.404 --> 17:53.364
if I don't go to the after-prom?
I'll still drop you off.

17:53.448 --> 17:55.992
I-I thought you were, um,

17:56.075 --> 17:57.952
I thought you were
spending the night.

18:00.371 --> 18:02.040
Belly, if I stay, I'm just gonna
ruin the rest of the night

18:02.123 --> 18:03.458
for you.
I don't want to do that.

18:03.541 --> 18:05.043
Did I, did I do something?

18:05.126 --> 18:06.795
♪ To the straight and narrow ♪

18:06.878 --> 18:09.005
♪ While the harlots
of my perils ♪

18:09.088 --> 18:11.800
Belly, can we please
just go outside and talk?

18:11.883 --> 18:14.511
♪ Scream ♪

18:16.387 --> 18:19.349
♪ And I...

18:19.432 --> 18:22.560
[music continues in distance]

18:38.743 --> 18:40.453
I'm sorry.

18:47.001 --> 18:51.089
I know this is hard
with everything going on.

18:53.091 --> 18:54.551
Please don't shut me out.

18:56.135 --> 18:59.013
I feel like I just
keep disappointing you.

18:59.097 --> 19:00.765
You haven't.

19:00.849 --> 19:02.559
- And you aren't.
- I have, I have.

19:02.642 --> 19:04.060
All I've done today
is disappoint you.

19:04.143 --> 19:05.228
You don't deserve that.

19:05.311 --> 19:07.063
Then just stop acting like this

19:07.146 --> 19:09.399
and come back inside with me.

19:10.441 --> 19:12.026
I can't.

19:14.070 --> 19:15.780
I just can't.

19:15.864 --> 19:17.907
[music continues in distance]

19:17.991 --> 19:19.534
[sighs]

19:21.870 --> 19:24.038
[Belly] Fine. Then...

19:24.122 --> 19:26.249
Then if you won't say it,
I will.

19:27.292 --> 19:28.459
Say what?

19:28.543 --> 19:30.378
That we're over.

19:32.130 --> 19:34.132
I mean, we are, aren't we?

19:35.133 --> 19:37.010
Belly...

19:37.093 --> 19:39.596
[voice breaking] No, don't.
Don't say anything.

19:42.891 --> 19:44.976
Belly, don't leave it like this.

19:45.059 --> 19:48.813
[crying] You... you are the one
that made it like this.

19:48.855 --> 19:50.398
No. No.

19:52.108 --> 19:54.527
- Belly, wait.
- [crying] Stop.

19:56.279 --> 19:57.655
Wait!

19:57.739 --> 20:01.200
♪ I'll always feel this,
no more promise...

20:01.284 --> 20:03.244
[sobbing]

20:03.328 --> 20:06.664
♪ No longer will I follow ♪

20:06.748 --> 20:09.626
♪ Can anybody hear me? ♪

20:09.709 --> 20:16.716
♪ I just want to be me ♪

20:16.799 --> 20:19.260
[engine starts]

20:19.344 --> 20:22.430
♪ And when I can ♪♪

20:22.513 --> 20:24.515
- [sobbing softly]
- Okay, come on.

20:29.646 --> 20:31.439
You know,
Conrad just pushes people away

20:31.522 --> 20:32.941
when he needs them most.

20:35.818 --> 20:38.321
There's only so many times
I can take being pushed.

20:38.404 --> 20:40.531
It's fucking exhausting.

20:43.076 --> 20:44.702
[softly] Yeah.

20:52.210 --> 20:54.087
[Jeremiah clears throat]

20:56.381 --> 20:58.132
- All right.
- All right.

20:58.216 --> 21:00.301
You ready?

21:00.385 --> 21:02.512
- We got this.
- Yeah.

21:05.723 --> 21:07.517
[sighs] Okay.

21:11.938 --> 21:13.147
Can I help you?

21:13.231 --> 21:14.691
Aunt Julia. Oh, my God!

21:14.774 --> 21:17.777
- [chuckles]
- Uh, um, Conrad told me
you were here.

21:17.860 --> 21:19.153
It's-it's been so long.
Just wanted to say hi.

21:19.237 --> 21:20.989
- Jeremiah.
- Yeah.

21:21.072 --> 21:22.073
And...?

21:22.156 --> 21:23.741
Um, Belly Conklin. Isabel.

21:23.825 --> 21:26.411
I'm Laurel Park's daughter,
Susannah's best friend.

21:26.494 --> 21:28.246
- Right. Sorry. Wow.
- [Belly] Yeah.

21:28.329 --> 21:30.331
- It's been so long.
- [Jeremiah] Yeah.

21:30.415 --> 21:33.376
You've really got my dad's eyes.

21:33.459 --> 21:37.046
Uh, I got these hydrangeas
for you from my mom's garden.

21:37.130 --> 21:38.548
- Oh.
- I was just wondering

21:38.631 --> 21:40.341
if we could have
a second to talk.

21:40.425 --> 21:41.968
Is this about the house?

21:42.051 --> 21:44.262
- Yeah. [chuckles]
- I'm sorry,

21:44.345 --> 21:46.305
but I've decided
to move ahead with the sale.

21:46.389 --> 21:49.559
Actually, we're-we're gonna
have an open house tomorrow.

21:49.642 --> 21:52.145
- Oh.
- Um, uh, you have to know

21:52.228 --> 21:55.440
how-how much the house means
to Jeremiah and Conrad

21:55.523 --> 21:56.899
and me and my family.

21:56.983 --> 21:58.901
I mean, you spent summers there
as a kid, right?

21:59.944 --> 22:02.071
- A few, yeah.
- [Belly] Yeah.

22:02.155 --> 22:04.115
I mean, then, you know,
why would you want

22:04.198 --> 22:06.743
to let go of
such a-a magical place?

22:07.910 --> 22:10.121
I remember
Susannah calling it that.

22:10.204 --> 22:12.832
You know, I-I don't understand
how you can just

22:12.915 --> 22:15.126
get rid of something
your sister loved so much.

22:15.209 --> 22:16.377
- I mean, it's kind of a...
- It's not personal.

22:17.545 --> 22:19.297
Yeah, I bet.

22:19.380 --> 22:22.717
Are you suggesting
that I gift the house to you?

22:22.800 --> 22:24.260
- I mean, it is our...
- No, no, of course not.

22:24.343 --> 22:25.720
Then I-I think
you and your brother

22:25.803 --> 22:27.180
should sort this out
with your dad.

22:27.263 --> 22:28.681
I'm certain that
you have the resources,

22:28.765 --> 22:30.391
but I can't put off a sale

22:30.475 --> 22:32.477
while I wait for you
to get your ducks in a row.

22:32.560 --> 22:35.146
I have to be
back at work in a week.

22:35.229 --> 22:37.148
I barely got
the time off as it is.

22:37.231 --> 22:40.109
So that's why you didn't
make it to the funeral?

22:42.653 --> 22:43.946
Something like that.

22:44.030 --> 22:45.073
- [Jeremiah] Mm.
- [Skye] Mom?

22:45.156 --> 22:47.366
- Yeah. Hi.
- Jeremiah?

22:47.450 --> 22:49.786
Skye? I-I didn't know
you were here.

22:50.828 --> 22:52.455
This is Belly.

22:52.538 --> 22:54.874
Um, her mom and mine
were best friends.

22:54.957 --> 22:56.292
I thought you were working on

22:56.375 --> 22:57.710
the virtual tour
for the open house?

22:57.794 --> 23:00.296
- Oh, I-I just
finished that, so...
- Okay.

23:00.379 --> 23:01.589
Let's eat.

23:01.672 --> 23:03.382
- Thanks for stopping by.
- [Jeremiah] Of course.

23:03.466 --> 23:05.468
- Yeah.
- Uh, don't forget
your flowers.

23:05.551 --> 23:06.636
- Oh. Thanks.
- Yeah, you should get those.

23:06.719 --> 23:08.387
- [Belly] Thank you.
- Bye-bye.

23:08.471 --> 23:10.765
- Have a, have a good
rest of your day.
- Nice to see you.

23:18.106 --> 23:19.690
So...

23:19.774 --> 23:21.567
what are you thinking about now?

23:21.651 --> 23:24.862
That I'm an idiot for thinking I
could change Aunt Julia's mind.

23:24.946 --> 23:26.823
Hey, you had to try.

23:32.120 --> 23:34.122
It's all up to Conrad now
and whether or not

23:34.205 --> 23:36.499
he can convince Dad
to dip into his trust.

23:36.582 --> 23:39.043
That's gonna go over well.

23:39.127 --> 23:40.419
It's still bad between them?

23:44.882 --> 23:47.385
You know, you and Conrad should
talk to your dad together.

23:47.468 --> 23:49.470
No, he's gonna try
to do it alone,

23:49.554 --> 23:51.180
and I'm sick of
fighting with him.

23:51.264 --> 23:52.640
All right, then don't.

23:52.723 --> 23:54.934
I mean,
you know, with Adam here,

23:55.017 --> 23:57.353
you two need to be
on the same team.

24:01.482 --> 24:03.317
Yeah, I'll give it a shot.

24:04.318 --> 24:06.362
- [phone chiming]
- Oh.

24:08.698 --> 24:10.241
Bad news?

24:11.284 --> 24:13.411
No, it's just, uh... [sighs]

24:13.494 --> 24:15.621
...volleyball girls group chat.

24:15.705 --> 24:17.999
All the stuff we have
to bring to camp next week.

24:18.082 --> 24:20.793
You don't seem like
you're looking forward to it.

24:20.877 --> 24:22.879
Yeah, I just...
I haven't had the best year.

24:22.962 --> 24:26.674
Um, I got demoted
from team captain.

24:28.426 --> 24:31.888
I kind of lost my shit
on everybody at regionals.

24:31.971 --> 24:34.599
Yeah, you do get kind of mean
when you play volleyball.

24:34.682 --> 24:35.933
Yeah, I like to win.

24:36.017 --> 24:37.727
Oh, believe me, I'm aware.

24:37.810 --> 24:40.354
[laughs] Isn't that
kind of, like,

24:40.438 --> 24:43.524
fiery, competitive,
a little bit sassy spirit

24:43.608 --> 24:46.319
kind of what they're looking for
in a volleyball captain?

24:46.402 --> 24:47.987
Normally, yeah, yes.

24:48.070 --> 24:49.280
But...

24:49.363 --> 24:53.743
But we were six points down
to a garbage team,

24:53.826 --> 24:55.912
and it was insanely hot
in their gym,

24:55.995 --> 24:58.873
and all of my spikes
kept going into the net.

24:58.956 --> 25:00.791
[sighs]

25:00.875 --> 25:03.586
I just... I couldn't focus.
I mean...

25:03.669 --> 25:05.213
[sighs]

25:06.464 --> 25:09.091
All I could think about
was Susannah.

25:13.971 --> 25:16.557
I just...

25:16.641 --> 25:18.809
I just lost it.

25:18.893 --> 25:20.937
I get it.

25:25.691 --> 25:27.026
[Jeremiah sighs]

25:27.109 --> 25:29.612
Yeah, so I kind of
promised Taylor

25:29.695 --> 25:32.907
that I would do
this volleyball camp.

25:32.990 --> 25:35.660
But who knows?
Maybe it was a bad idea.

25:35.743 --> 25:37.245
No, you're doing the camp, okay?

25:37.328 --> 25:38.913
If I have to deal with Conrad,

25:38.996 --> 25:41.207
then you are gonna show up
for your team. Deal?

25:41.290 --> 25:43.834
- Deal. Mm-hmm.
- Yes.

25:48.047 --> 25:50.341
I really missed you, Jere.

25:53.469 --> 25:56.389
[♪ Remi Wolf: "Pink + White"]

25:56.430 --> 25:58.391
[message chirps]

26:01.310 --> 26:02.812
- Eyes on the road.
- Oh, come on.

26:02.895 --> 26:05.648
- I saw you look at my phone.
- Don't flatter yourself.

26:05.731 --> 26:07.233
Yeah, whatever.
Don't look at my phone.

26:07.275 --> 26:10.987
♪ That's the way
every day goes...

26:11.070 --> 26:13.030
You sure Milo's cool
with you coming with me?

26:13.114 --> 26:14.490
Of course. Why wouldn't he be?

26:14.573 --> 26:16.867
[scoffs]

26:16.951 --> 26:19.036
[chuckles] Because of, uh...

26:21.038 --> 26:22.957
...la-last summer.

26:22.999 --> 26:25.501
♪ Nod my head,
don't close my eyes...

26:25.584 --> 26:27.878
Last summer?

26:27.962 --> 26:30.423
[laughs]

26:30.506 --> 26:33.175
Because we kissed
for like two seconds?

26:33.259 --> 26:35.303
No. He's fine.

26:35.386 --> 26:36.345
- [message chirps]
- He says hi.

26:36.429 --> 26:37.930
[scoffs] Yeah, sure.

26:38.014 --> 26:39.557
What do you mean, "Yeah, sure"?
"Tell Steve-o what's up."

26:39.640 --> 26:41.225
Okay. Okay, okay. You...

26:41.309 --> 26:42.560
- You're the one who told me
eyes on the road.
- Okay.

26:42.643 --> 26:44.103
Okay, can you not yell at me
right now, please?

26:44.186 --> 26:46.022
[stammers]

26:46.063 --> 26:49.150
♪ It's the same way
you showed me ♪

26:50.401 --> 26:54.113
♪ Showed me ♪

26:54.155 --> 26:57.533
♪ And you showed me love ♪

26:59.910 --> 27:02.788
- [message chirps]
- ♪ And the glory from above ♪

27:02.872 --> 27:03.873
[message chirps]

27:03.956 --> 27:06.667
♪ Regard, my dear...

27:08.711 --> 27:10.421
Everything cool?

27:10.504 --> 27:12.298
Yeah.

27:12.381 --> 27:13.549
[chuckles softly]

27:13.632 --> 27:15.176
What? Is Mr.
I Don't Believe In College

27:15.259 --> 27:16.761
having an existential crisis?

27:16.844 --> 27:19.472
[scoffs] God, does he even know
what "existential" means?

27:19.555 --> 27:21.891
[laughs] I bet you
he thinks "SAT"

27:21.974 --> 27:24.018
- stands for "stupid-ass test."
- Can I tell you something?

27:24.101 --> 27:27.730
Not everyone measures people's
worth by what Ivy they go to.

27:27.813 --> 27:29.190
Like, you know that, right?

27:29.273 --> 27:30.941
Those schools are
just full of assholes

27:31.025 --> 27:32.943
who think that
they run the world.

27:33.027 --> 27:36.781
Then again, you are the guy
who berated his grieving sister

27:36.864 --> 27:38.407
in front of
an entire party, so...

27:38.491 --> 27:40.743
I don't know.

27:40.826 --> 27:42.578
Maybe you'll fit right in.

27:44.497 --> 27:46.040
I didn't berate her.

27:46.123 --> 27:47.958
- Yeah, you kind of did.
- [turns music up]

27:48.042 --> 27:49.543
♪ That birthed you ♪

27:49.627 --> 27:51.962
♪ Gave you tools
just to stay alive ♪

27:52.046 --> 27:54.298
♪ And make it out
when the sun is ruined ♪

27:54.382 --> 27:57.843
♪ That's the same way
you showed me ♪

27:57.927 --> 28:00.679
♪ Showed me ♪♪

28:02.640 --> 28:04.767
You guys went to the store?

28:04.850 --> 28:07.186
Uh, we actually thought
about leaving,

28:07.269 --> 28:09.980
but then we decided
not to listen to you.

28:10.064 --> 28:13.192
We didn't just get groceries.

28:13.275 --> 28:15.361
We actually went
to see Aunt Julia.

28:15.444 --> 28:16.946
How did that go?

28:18.572 --> 28:19.990
Not great.

28:21.492 --> 28:23.160
Talk to Dad yet?

28:23.244 --> 28:24.370
No.

28:25.413 --> 28:27.748
Um, I'm-I'm gonna
take these inside.

28:27.832 --> 28:29.166
Thanks.

28:33.379 --> 28:35.047
How were the waves?

28:35.131 --> 28:38.134
Uh... break's a little choppy.

28:38.217 --> 28:41.554
Maybe we should go out later
when it's, uh, smooth out.

28:41.637 --> 28:43.514
All right.

28:46.267 --> 28:48.018
Hey, listen, um...

28:50.104 --> 28:52.022
I want to be there
when you talk to Dad.

28:52.106 --> 28:54.817
I'm-I'm better with him lately,
and once he sees

28:54.900 --> 28:56.819
how passionate we are
about keeping the house,

28:56.902 --> 28:58.362
he'll have to let us
use our trusts.

28:58.446 --> 29:00.156
Our trusts?

29:00.239 --> 29:01.991
No more doing everything alone.

29:04.285 --> 29:05.494
All right.

29:05.578 --> 29:07.371
Cool.

29:16.005 --> 29:18.591
I can drive
the last leg if you want.

29:37.318 --> 29:38.819
[Taylor sighs]

29:39.945 --> 29:42.448
- Look...
- Wha... Are you...?

29:42.531 --> 29:44.325
I don't actually think
that you're a shitty brother.

29:44.408 --> 29:46.160
Oh, wow. Thanks a lot.

29:46.243 --> 29:48.120
No, I think it's really cool
that you're going to Princeton.

29:48.204 --> 29:50.998
I know you worked
really hard for it.

29:51.081 --> 29:52.458
It's just...

29:53.959 --> 29:56.879
...sometimes it feels like
you think that you're better

29:56.962 --> 29:58.589
and smarter than everyone.

29:59.798 --> 30:01.759
Uh, including me.

30:01.842 --> 30:04.678
Taylor, I don't
think that at all.

30:04.762 --> 30:06.472
You're one of
the smartest people I know.

30:07.515 --> 30:09.725
Whatever.
I mean, I definitely am.

30:13.771 --> 30:16.315
Can you tell me what has you
all in your feelings

30:16.398 --> 30:18.484
so that it can stop being weird?

30:18.567 --> 30:19.652
Please?

30:21.278 --> 30:24.198
Does Belly really think I don't
care about Susannah's death?

30:24.281 --> 30:26.700
Steven, of course
she doesn't think that.

30:26.784 --> 30:29.578
Belly was having
a really shitty night.

30:31.288 --> 30:33.374
Yeah, I know.

30:33.457 --> 30:35.793
I mean, like, I...

30:35.876 --> 30:37.461
I miss Susannah.

30:37.545 --> 30:39.004
You know? But I'm also,

30:39.088 --> 30:41.799
like, really excited
for Princeton now.

30:42.841 --> 30:44.301
Am I an asshole?

30:45.970 --> 30:47.805
Probably, but that's not why.

30:49.640 --> 30:51.100
[Steven chuckles softly]

30:53.185 --> 30:57.273
Steven, everyone processes
things differently, you know?

30:57.356 --> 30:59.358
I mean, my therapist says

30:59.441 --> 31:01.527
that happiness and grief
can coexist.

31:01.610 --> 31:03.195
And that's completely fine.

31:06.782 --> 31:07.866
Okay.

31:08.909 --> 31:10.494
Okay.

31:12.913 --> 31:15.124
I'll, uh...

31:15.207 --> 31:17.001
I'll talk to Belly
when we get there.

31:17.084 --> 31:19.003
Okay?

31:19.086 --> 31:20.671
[laughs]

31:22.631 --> 31:24.049
[laughs]

31:25.092 --> 31:27.928
Um, and since we're...

31:28.012 --> 31:31.181
well, you know,
since we're sharing, uh...

31:32.725 --> 31:35.519
...I guess
I should mention, um...

31:35.603 --> 31:37.396
They don't exactly know
we're coming.

31:37.479 --> 31:38.689
What?

31:38.772 --> 31:40.608
Yeah, Conrad didn't
actually ask me to c...

31:40.691 --> 31:42.484
uh, come to Cousins,
but, you know, that's...

31:42.568 --> 31:44.612
So we just drove all day
to show up somewhere uninvited?

31:44.695 --> 31:46.572
Look, I wanted to be there
for them, all right?

31:46.655 --> 31:48.741
So I invited myself. I'm sorry.

31:48.824 --> 31:50.242
I get it. I get it.

31:50.326 --> 31:53.912
It's like,
whatever happens, just...

31:53.996 --> 31:56.332
please don't take it personally.

31:56.415 --> 31:58.375
Like, even I can tell
that the Fisher boys

31:58.459 --> 32:00.252
love you to death, Steven.

32:01.295 --> 32:02.421
Let's go.

32:05.299 --> 32:07.843
Also, gate crashing 101 says
we can't show up empty-handed,

32:07.926 --> 32:10.471
so keep an eye out
for somewhere to stop.

32:10.554 --> 32:12.556
Just don't change
my seat setting.

32:12.640 --> 32:15.059
- No, the car is, like...
- No, it's not the car.

32:15.142 --> 32:16.310
It's you.

32:16.393 --> 32:18.312
- Don't blame my car.
- It's not me.

32:19.355 --> 32:21.273
Dad should be calling soon.

32:21.357 --> 32:23.067
Yeah.

32:23.150 --> 32:24.568
Do you guys want
to talk to him alone?

32:24.652 --> 32:26.612
- I can wait upstairs.
- No, stay. Stay.

32:26.695 --> 32:27.988
You helped me and J
get this far.

32:28.072 --> 32:30.949
Plus, it's your house
as much as it is ours.

32:31.033 --> 32:33.243
[cell phone ringing]

32:38.248 --> 32:39.917
- Dad, hey.
- [Adam] Hey, Con.

32:40.000 --> 32:42.544
I only got
about a few minutes here.

32:42.628 --> 32:44.171
- Hey, Dad.
- Jere?

32:44.254 --> 32:45.589
You're in Cousins, too?

32:45.673 --> 32:47.299
Yeah, just got here last night.

32:47.383 --> 32:49.760
All right, look, I got
a heads-up from the bank

32:49.843 --> 32:52.054
