that's not true.

39:17.147 --> 39:19.399
Jere, come on.
You get it, don't you?

39:19.483 --> 39:22.486
[sighs] Dad, I-I don't,
I don't get why

39:22.569 --> 39:24.404
we can't just use
our trust to buy it,

39:24.488 --> 39:27.616
and then we can sell it later
if we need the money.

39:27.699 --> 39:30.994
No. Julia's gonna go ahead
with the open house tomorrow.

39:31.078 --> 39:32.621
I really appreciate
the attempt here,

39:32.704 --> 39:34.414
but this is the end
of the conversation.

39:34.498 --> 39:37.250
You just make sure that Julia
gets everything that she needs.

39:37.334 --> 39:38.752
- You got it?
- Conrad was right.

39:38.835 --> 39:41.004
Talking to you is pointless.

39:42.005 --> 39:43.799
♪ ♪

39:51.389 --> 39:53.183
Surprise!

39:53.266 --> 39:54.893
Oh, shit.

39:54.976 --> 39:56.937
I-I knew we should have
told them we were coming.

39:57.020 --> 39:59.231
No, it's not that. It's...

39:59.314 --> 40:01.066
We're losing the house.

40:01.149 --> 40:04.194
- They put it up for sale.
- Oh, Cinderbelly...

40:04.277 --> 40:07.239
- They're selling the house?
- Yeah.

40:11.159 --> 40:14.496
Um, I-I brought you blueberry.

40:16.206 --> 40:17.833
I'm glad you're here.

40:22.045 --> 40:24.297
[♪ Mac Miller: "Circles"]

40:24.381 --> 40:25.924
♪ Well ♪

40:26.007 --> 40:28.718
